Following the conclusion of the Spanish La Liga Match Day 18 fixtures on Sunday, below are the highest goal scorers chasing the golden boot in the Spanish top-flight league. Barcelona captain, Lionel Messi is currently the highest goal scorer in the La Liga with 13 goals after he scored a goal in his side’s 4-1 victory against Alaves over the weekend. Real Madrid striker, Karim Benzema is in the second position with 12 goals after he failed to score in his side’s 0-0 draw against Athletic Bilbao on Sunday. La Liga top scorers: 13 goals: Lionel Messi (Barcelona) 12 goals: Karim Benzema (Real Madrid) 10 goals: Luis Suarez (Barcelona) 8 goals: Lucas Perez (Alaves), Gerard Moreno (Villarreal), Loren Moron (Real Betis), Chimy Avila (Osasuna), Angel Rodriguez (Gatefe), Roger Martí (Levante). 7 goals: Antoine Griezmann (Barcelona), Willian Jose (Real Sociedad), Mikel Oyarzabal (Real Sociedad), Alvaro Morata (Atletico Madrid), Joselu (Alaves), Iago Aspas (Celta Vigo) 6 goals: Maxi Gomez (Valencia), Daniel Parejo (Valencia), Joaquín (Real Betis), Karl Toko Ekambi (Villareal), Ante Budimir(Mallorca) The La Liga Match Day 19 fixtures will commence on January 3. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.